title: Quake aftershock hits duvall
author: Seattle Times Staffseattle Times News Services
text: DUVALL - A moderate earthquake rattled the Duvall area yesterday, one of the biggest aftershocks to the 5.4 earthquake that shook the Puget Sound region May 2.     The 3.0 magnitude aftershock, also felt in the Monroe area about nine miles north of Duvall, struck at 3:04 p.m. and was centered 5.2 miles northeast of Duvall, according to the University of Washington seismology lab.     No injuries or major damage were caused, said Jan Jorgensen, Snohomish County Sheriff's Office spokeswoman.     About 400 aftershocks have occurred within two miles of the quake's epicenter, said Bill Steele, UW seismology-lab coordinator. The largest aftershock, on May 4, had a 3.6 magnitude.
